.TH man_1_simple_shell 1


.SH NAME

.B simple_shell-
computer program that exposes an operating system's services to a human user or other programs


.SH SYNOPSIS

 ./hsh (name of the executable file)


.SH DESCRIPTION

.B simple_shell,
is a custom implementation of a simple UNIX shell.

 Simply put, the shell is a program that takes commands from the keyboard and gives them to the operating system to perform.

This is simply my own (incomplete but working) version of simple_shell


.SH COMPILING

-The GNU Compiler Collectiojn, gcc, is recommended for compiling simple_shell with extra flags as shown.
.P
.RS
.B $ gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh
.P

-In interactive mode, the simple_shell works by taking user input on the terminal after pressing the enter key. Note that the prompt ('$') will appear and you will then be in interactive mode and able to enter commands followed by "enter."

.P
.RS
.B $ ./hsh
.P

-In non-interactive mode, users can specify shell scripts to be executed by simple_shell usually through the use of pipes '|'.

.P
.RS
.B echo 'pwd' | ./hsh


.SH EXECUTABLES

Example of executables:
.IP
.br
.\&
.RS
\&$ echo "Example of executables"
.br
\&"Example of executables"
.br
\&$


